WEBVTT

00:08.050 --> 00:09.885
- YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
LAST WEEK?

00:09.885 --> 00:11.053
WELL, I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO TELL YOU.

00:11.053 --> 00:12.471
I'M BUSY.

00:12.471 --> 00:14.223
OH!

00:14.223 --> 00:16.059
- WHAT'S YOUR DAD GONNA DO
WHEN HE GETS OUT OF JAIL

00:16.059 --> 00:17.601
AND I TELL HIM YOU SPEND ALL DAY
WITH ORANGE BOY

00:17.601 --> 00:18.811
RUBBING YOUR DICKS TOGETHER?

00:18.811 --> 00:21.021
$500 TOMORROW,
OR I CALL HIM.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.606
- THE DAY MY BABIES ARE BORN,

00:22.606 --> 00:24.692
YOU STEAL CASH
FROM THE REGISTER?

00:24.692 --> 00:26.569
- YEAH, YOUR REGISTER,
MY CASH.

00:26.569 --> 00:28.154
- EMPTY YOUR FUCKING POCKETS.

00:28.154 --> 00:29.989
- HE'S A FUCKING DEAD MAN.

00:29.989 --> 00:31.449
- WELL, HELLO.

00:31.449 --> 00:33.367
ROGER RUNNING TREE AND I
BROKE UP.

00:33.367 --> 00:35.744
BUT THE CHILDREN, FRANK.

00:35.744 --> 00:38.914
ROGER AND I--WE WERE GONNA
GET MARRIED AND ADOPT THEM

00:38.914 --> 00:40.833
BEFORE HE SHOWED
HIS TRUE COLORS.

00:40.833 --> 00:43.002
ALL I NEED
IS A MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE.

00:43.002 --> 00:44.962
FRANK, WILL YOU MARRY ME?

00:44.962 --> 00:47.840
- IT IS MY HONOR TO DECLARE YOU
MAN AND WIFE.

00:47.840 --> 00:48.674
YOU MAY KISS THE GROOM.

00:48.674 --> 00:50.259
[applause]

00:50.259 --> 00:51.719
- HE'S IN SERIOUS CONDITION,

00:51.719 --> 00:52.887
SO THEY MOVED HIM
UP THE WAITING LIST.

00:52.887 --> 00:54.139
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

00:54.139 --> 00:55.931
- HE'S GETTING A LIVER.
- WHAT?

00:55.931 --> 00:57.766
- NEED YOU TO MEET MY MOM
AND DAD FOR PARENTS' WEEKEND.

00:57.766 --> 00:58.851
PRETEND WE'RE TOGETHER.

00:58.851 --> 00:59.852
- JUST CLEAN UP FOR A DINNER?

00:59.852 --> 01:01.103
- NO, NO CLEANUP.

01:01.103 --> 01:02.813
I NEED TO SCARE THE LIVING SHIT
OUT OF THEM.

01:02.813 --> 01:04.149
- THOSE YOUR BROTHERS
AND SISTERS?

01:04.149 --> 01:05.483
- FOUR OF THEM,
THREE MORE IN THE VAN.

01:05.483 --> 01:07.193
MY FAMILY LIVES IN THERE.

01:07.193 --> 01:08.278
- IN THE SUPERMARKET?

01:08.278 --> 01:10.029
- NO, IN THE VAN.

01:10.029 --> 01:11.071
- OH.

01:11.071 --> 01:12.281
- HEY, MATTHEW.

01:12.281 --> 01:13.532
- WHAT DOES SHE HAVE
THAT I DON'T?

01:13.532 --> 01:15.160
- HELLO?

01:15.160 --> 01:17.036
- YOU DON'T KNOW
WHO YOU MESSED WITH, SKANK.

01:17.036 --> 01:19.622
- [screams]

01:19.622 --> 01:21.499
I DON'T GIVE A SHIT
IF YOU'RE TEN YEARS OLD

01:21.499 --> 01:22.625
AND PLAYING WITH DOLLS.

01:22.625 --> 01:24.460
YOU WANT A WAR,
YOU GOT IT.

01:24.460 --> 01:26.254
- FIONA NEVER CAME HOME.

01:26.254 --> 01:27.129
SHE VIOLATED PROBATION.

01:27.129 --> 01:29.340
- HI, LIP.
I'M SORRY.

01:29.340 --> 01:30.716
I FUCKED UP.

01:30.716 --> 01:32.302
YOU'RE JUGGLING SO MANY THINGS,

01:32.302 --> 01:34.470
AND I AM JUST FUCKING UP.

01:34.470 --> 01:36.138
I NEED SOME HELP NOW.

01:36.138 --> 01:39.683
- SO YOU WANT TO GO FIRST?

01:47.691 --> 01:50.569
[High Strung's
The Luck You Got]

01:50.569 --> 01:54.615
♪ ♪

01:54.615 --> 01:58.035
- ♪ THINK OF ALL THE LUCK
YOU GOT ♪

01:58.035 --> 02:01.164
♪ KNOW THAT
IT'S NOT FOR NAUGHT ♪

02:01.164 --> 02:04.167
♪ YOU WERE BEAMING
ONCE BEFORE ♪

02:04.167 --> 02:08.212
♪ BUT IT'S NOT LIKE THAT
ANYMORE ♪

02:08.212 --> 02:11.757
♪ WHAT IS THIS DOWNSIDE ♪

02:11.757 --> 02:15.345
♪ THAT YOU SPEAK OF? ♪

02:15.345 --> 02:17.388
♪ WHAT IS THIS FEELING ♪

02:17.388 --> 02:22.101
♪ YOU'RE SO SURE OF? ♪

02:22.101 --> 02:29.108
♪ ♪

02:29.108 --> 02:32.320
♪ ROUND UP THE FRIENDS
YOU GOT ♪

02:32.320 --> 02:35.322
♪ KNOW THAT
THEY'RE NOT FOR NAUGHT ♪

02:35.322 --> 02:38.534
♪ YOU WERE WILLING
ONCE BEFORE ♪

02:38.534 --> 02:42.955
♪ BUT IT'S NOT LIKE THAT
ANYMORE ♪

02:42.955 --> 02:46.376
♪ WHAT IS THIS DOWNSIDE ♪

02:46.376 --> 02:49.962
♪ THAT YOU SPEAK OF? ♪

02:49.962 --> 02:51.797
♪ WHAT IS THIS FEELING ♪

02:51.797 --> 02:55.551
♪ YOU'RE SO SURE OF? ♪

03:15.487 --> 03:17.114
- WHERE ARE WE GOING?

03:17.114 --> 03:19.366
- LOOKS LIKE
DECATUR CORRECTIONAL.

03:19.366 --> 03:20.701
- HOW FAR AWAY IS THAT?

03:20.701 --> 03:22.370
- THREE HOURS OR SO.

03:22.370 --> 03:23.245
- WHAT?

03:23.245 --> 03:24.872
- HOPE YOU PEED.

03:26.957 --> 03:28.251
- [sighs]

03:28.251 --> 03:30.210
- WHAT'D THEY NAB YOU FOR?

03:30.210 --> 03:31.211
- HUH?

03:31.211 --> 03:32.379
- WHY YOU ON THIS BUS?

03:32.379 --> 03:35.425
IT AIN'T A SIGHTSEEING TOUR.

03:35.425 --> 03:37.635
- I, UH...

03:37.635 --> 03:41.306
I BROKE PROBATION.

03:41.306 --> 03:44.183
- I STABBED MY BOYFRIEND'S WIFE
IN THE STOMACH A LITTLE BIT.

03:44.183 --> 03:45.893
BITCH CLAIMED
SHE WAS PREGNANT.

03:45.893 --> 03:47.227
KNEW SHE WAS FULL OF SHIT

03:47.227 --> 03:49.355
AND WAS SAYING IT
TO HOLD ON TO HIM.

03:49.355 --> 03:51.815
HAD TO PROVE HER WRONG, RIGHT?

03:51.815 --> 03:53.984
TURNS OUT SHE WASN'T LYING.

03:53.984 --> 03:55.445
OOPS.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.115
- HEY, POPS.

04:00.115 --> 04:02.534
HOW YOU FEELING?

04:02.534 --> 04:04.536
YOU ARE LOOKING BETTER TODAY.

04:04.536 --> 04:06.163
SAY HI TO YOUR GRANDPA,
CHUCKIE.

04:06.163 --> 04:08.207
- CAN HE HEAR US?
- OF COURSE HE CAN.

04:08.207 --> 04:10.376
THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
HE'S GONNA WAKE UP.

04:10.376 --> 04:11.794
WHEN WE TELL HIM
HOW WE FEEL,

04:11.794 --> 04:14.380
IT SEEPS
INTO HIS SUBCONSCIOUS,

04:14.380 --> 04:16.173
IT TICKLES HIS BRAIN,

04:16.173 --> 04:18.008
AND IT'LL MAKE HIM
OPEN HIS EYES SOON, OKAY?

04:18.008 --> 04:19.885
COME ON.
- OKAY.

04:21.178 --> 04:22.805
HI, GRANDPA.

04:22.805 --> 04:25.182
MAMA SAYS WE CAN GO
TO RUBY TUESDAY'S

04:25.182 --> 04:26.350
WHEN YOU WAKE UP.

04:26.350 --> 04:27.476
- HI.

04:27.476 --> 04:29.019
- GOOD MORNING.

04:29.019 --> 04:30.062
- I'M EMILY.

04:30.062 --> 04:31.313
I NEED A NEW HEART.

04:31.313 --> 04:33.607
- OH, I'M SO SORRY.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.443
- WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOURS?

04:35.443 --> 04:37.152
- HEY, DON'T BE RUDE.

04:37.152 --> 04:38.320
- OH, MY GOD.

04:38.320 --> 04:40.906
- DON'T YOU "OH, MY GOD" ME,
MISTER.

04:40.906 --> 04:43.242
THIS IS MY SON,
CHUCKIE.

04:43.242 --> 04:44.284
I'M SAMMI.

04:44.284 --> 04:46.120
- I'M WENDY, HER MOM.

04:46.120 --> 04:48.872
SHE, UH...
SHE HAS CARDIOMYOPATHY.

04:48.872 --> 04:50.874
- MY HEART MUSCLE
DOESN'T PUMP ENOUGH BLOOD

04:50.874 --> 04:52.418
INTO THE REST OF MY BODY.

04:52.418 --> 04:54.128
- IS THAT WHY YOU LOOK
LIKE A VAMPIRE?

04:54.128 --> 04:57.047
- HEY, CHARLES NEVINS SLOTT,
YOU STOP THAT RIGHT NOW.

04:57.047 --> 04:58.132
APOLOGIZE.

04:58.132 --> 04:59.633
- I'M SORRY.

04:59.633 --> 05:00.926
- WE ARE SO SORRY.

05:00.926 --> 05:02.720
- OH, GOD.
- IT'S OKAY.

05:02.720 --> 05:04.012
IT'S OKAY.

05:04.012 --> 05:06.140
- IS MR. GALLAGHER
YOUR FATHER?

05:06.140 --> 05:07.266
- SURE IS.

05:07.266 --> 05:09.435
- I DON'T HAVE A FATHER.

05:09.435 --> 05:11.729
- EMILY.
- HE LEFT WHEN I GOT SICK.

05:11.729 --> 05:14.940
MAMA SAYS THAT MEN CAN'T
HANDLE TRAGEDY, SO THEY LEAVE.

05:14.940 --> 05:17.317
- NOT EVERYBODY NEEDS TO HEAR
OUR DIRTY LAUNDRY, EMILY.

05:17.317 --> 05:18.610
- NO, DON'T WORRY ABOUT US.

05:18.610 --> 05:20.404
WE HAVE THE DIRTIEST LAUNDRY
IN CHICAGO.

05:20.404 --> 05:21.947
- [laughs]

05:21.947 --> 05:25.200
- IS MR. GALLAGHER
WAITING FOR A HEART TOO?

05:25.200 --> 05:28.120
- HE WAS WAITING FOR A LIVER,

05:28.120 --> 05:30.080
AND THEN HE HAD A TRANSPLANT
THE OTHER DAY,

05:30.080 --> 05:32.375
AND NOW HE IS GETTING
ALL BETTER.

05:32.375 --> 05:35.210
- THAT'S FANTASTIC NEWS.

05:35.210 --> 05:38.213
SEE, EMILY?
WE'RE IN THE RIGHT PLACE.

05:48.557 --> 05:50.560
- MICKEY YOUR BOYFRIEND?

05:50.560 --> 05:52.520
- WE HANG OUT.

05:52.520 --> 05:54.021
- HE'S IN YOUR BED.

05:54.021 --> 05:55.898
- YEAH, HIS FAMILY
IS A NIGHTMARE.

05:55.898 --> 05:57.567
- THINK I GOT A GIRLFRIEND.

05:57.567 --> 05:58.776
- OH, YEAH?

05:58.776 --> 06:00.319
- YEAH, HER FAMILY'S
A NIGHTMARE TOO.

06:00.319 --> 06:02.070
- WHOSE ISN'T?

06:02.070 --> 06:04.239
- YOU LOVE MICKEY?

06:04.239 --> 06:06.700
- I LIKE HOW HE SMELLS.

06:06.700 --> 06:09.119
- WHAT YOU ASKING
STUPID FUCKING QUESTIONS FOR?

06:09.119 --> 06:11.038
- YOU WERE NICER
WHEN YOU WERE ASLEEP.

06:11.038 --> 06:12.790
FRANK SURVIVED
HIS LIVER TRANSPLANT,

06:12.790 --> 06:13.957
IN CASE YOU WERE WONDERING.

06:13.957 --> 06:15.584
- NOPE. WASN'T.

06:15.584 --> 06:18.546
- I GOT TO GO OVER TO THE CHURCH
FOR THE CHRISTENING TODAY.

06:18.546 --> 06:19.797
- THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T CARE.

06:19.797 --> 06:22.007
- I DON'T.
- WHY ARE YOU GOING, THEN?

06:22.007 --> 06:24.468
- IT'S MY SON, MAN.

06:24.468 --> 06:26.845
- ALL RIGHT,
I'LL GET DRESSED.

06:26.845 --> 06:29.515
- NO, NO, LOOK,
IT'S FINE.

06:29.515 --> 06:30.891
I'LL HEAD OVER
BY MYSELF.

06:30.891 --> 06:32.601
I'LL BE BACK
IN A COUPLE HOURS.

06:32.601 --> 06:34.144
- WHAT,
YOU DON'T WANT ME TO GO?

06:36.021 --> 06:38.524
- PROBABLY BEST IF YOU DON'T,
TOUGH GUY.

06:38.524 --> 06:40.776
- YEAH, FOR YOU, MAYBE.

06:40.776 --> 06:42.986
- WHY YOU BUSTING
MY BALLS, MAN?

06:46.949 --> 06:49.952
- JUST WONDERING
IF WE'RE A COUPLE OR NOT.

06:55.374 --> 06:56.626
- OF COURSE WE ARE.

06:56.626 --> 06:58.168
- A COUPLE THAT HIDES?

06:58.168 --> 07:00.379
- HEY, IT'S WORKING OUT
SO FAR, SO GOOD.

07:00.379 --> 07:01.547
- GETTING KIND OF SICK OF IT.

07:01.547 --> 07:04.299
- JESUS CHRIST, MAN.

07:04.299 --> 07:05.968
HOW ABOUT YOU LET ME GO DEAL
WITH THAT STUPID SHIT

07:05.968 --> 07:07.886
BEFORE I DEAL
WITH YOUR STUPID SHIT?

07:07.886 --> 07:10.889
[The Peach Kings'
Fisherman]

07:10.889 --> 07:14.726
♪ ♪

07:14.726 --> 07:16.645
- HEY.

07:16.645 --> 07:18.355
- HOW WAS WORK, DEAR?

07:18.355 --> 07:21.191
- I GOT, UH,
MATCHING WAR WOUNDS.

07:21.191 --> 07:22.359
- OUCH.

07:22.359 --> 07:25.488
♪ ♪

07:25.488 --> 07:26.572
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

07:26.572 --> 07:28.407
- LOOKING UP
YOUR QUARTER GRADES.

07:28.407 --> 07:29.783
THEY HAVEN'T POSTED YET.

07:29.783 --> 07:31.451
- ALL RIGHT, GOOD.
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.745
I'M TOO STRESSED TO DEAL
RIGHT NOW.

07:33.745 --> 07:35.539
- THE WAY I SEE IT,
YOU NEED A "B" AVERAGE

07:35.539 --> 07:37.082
TO KEEP YOUR SCHOLARSHIP.

07:37.082 --> 07:39.001
- AND I DON'T WANT TO TALK
ABOUT IT EITHER.

07:39.001 --> 07:41.420
- I BET YOU'LL GET A "B"
IN MACRO AND PHILOSOPHY

07:41.420 --> 07:43.171
AND AN "A"
IN THERMO AND ENGLISH.

07:43.171 --> 07:45.966
- WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO
TO GET YOU TO SHUT UP?

07:47.510 --> 07:48.677
- WELL, MAYBE IF I HAD
SOMETHING ELSE

07:48.677 --> 07:51.221
TO OCCUPY MY MOUTH.

07:51.221 --> 07:53.307
- THAT'S A MUCH BETTER IDEA.

07:56.686 --> 07:57.728
ALL RIGHT.

07:57.728 --> 07:59.730
♪ ♪

07:59.730 --> 08:01.648
- WAIT. DON'T.
- WHY?

08:01.648 --> 08:03.108
- LEVELS THE PLAYING FIELD.

08:03.108 --> 08:04.484
I'M ON MY KNEES.
YOU'RE WEARING A HAIRNET.

08:04.484 --> 08:05.611
- YOU'RE A FREAK.

08:05.611 --> 08:07.154
- TAKES ONE TO KNOW ONE.

08:09.406 --> 08:11.074
- [sighs]

08:11.074 --> 08:12.951
OH, HEY, LOOK, UM,
I'M NOT GONNA BE ABLE

08:12.951 --> 08:15.537
TO HAVE DINNER
WITH YOUR PARENTS TONIGHT, OKAY?

08:15.537 --> 08:17.372
NO, YOU COULD KEEP DOING
WHAT YOU WERE DOING

08:17.372 --> 08:18.874
WHILE WE'RE TALKI--
OW, FUCK!

08:18.874 --> 08:20.626
- WHY WON'T YOU BE ABLE
TO GO, HMM?

08:20.626 --> 08:22.669
YOU SAID YOU WOULD GO.
YOU'RE--YOU'RE GOING.

08:22.669 --> 08:24.714
- NO, LOOK, I-I GOT TO--
I GOT TO GO HOME.

08:24.714 --> 08:25.964
I GOT TO FIGURE SHIT OUT,

08:25.964 --> 08:27.550
SEE HOW WE'RE GONNA
PAY THE BILLS

08:27.550 --> 08:28.550
FOR THE NEXT 90 DAYS
WHILE FIONA'S IN PRISON.

08:28.550 --> 08:30.302
- WE MADE A DEAL.

08:30.302 --> 08:31.803
- YEAH, THAT WAS BEFORE
MY SISTER WENT ON A BENDER.

08:31.803 --> 08:33.639
- YOU PROMISED TO HELP
TERRORIZE MY PARENTS

08:33.639 --> 08:35.558
IN EXCHANGE FOR ME
GIVING YOU STUFF.

08:35.558 --> 08:37.643
- OKAY, THEN HOW ABOUT
WE GET LUNCH TOMORROW?

08:37.643 --> 08:38.936
- NO, THEY'RE LEAVING FOR MIAMI
IN THE MORNING.

08:38.936 --> 08:40.437
A-A DEAL'S A DEAL.

08:40.437 --> 08:41.855
- YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
NOT HEARING ME.

08:41.855 --> 08:43.857
- AND YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
NOT A MAN OF YOUR WORD.

08:43.857 --> 08:51.865
♪ ♪

08:53.659 --> 08:55.703
- I WOULD TOTALLY HOOK UP
WITH MR. GEORGE.

08:55.703 --> 08:56.662
HE'S FOXY.

08:56.662 --> 08:58.330
- BUT HE'S MARRIED.

08:58.330 --> 08:59.581
- AND OLD.

08:59.581 --> 09:01.541
- THIS IS JUST
OUR FANTASY TEACHER LIST.

09:01.541 --> 09:02.668
IT DOESN'T MEAN
IT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

09:02.668 --> 09:05.003
- HMM, OH.

09:05.003 --> 09:08.256
- UGH, THAT SMELL
IS GONNA MAKE ME GAG.

09:08.256 --> 09:10.717
- DO WE REALLY HAVE TO DO
THIS STUPID BIOLOGY LAB?

09:12.260 --> 09:14.846
- [gasping]

09:14.846 --> 09:16.556
THERE'S HENRY MCNALLY.

09:16.556 --> 09:19.810
HE'S SO BANG-TASTIC.

09:19.810 --> 09:21.561
- I WANT TO SUCK HIM
LIKE A SLUSHEE.

09:21.561 --> 09:24.022
- HE MAKES MY LOINS ROAR
WITH HUNGER.

09:24.022 --> 09:26.566
- [laughs]

09:28.777 --> 09:30.487
- HEY, DEBBIE, HOW'S IT GOING?

09:31.739 --> 09:33.240
- ME?
- HER?

09:33.240 --> 09:35.492
- YEAH, I CAN HELP YOU
WITH YOUR LAB IF YOU WANT.

09:35.492 --> 09:39.287
- YOU KNOW MY NAME?
- [laughs] YEAH.

09:39.287 --> 09:41.707
- [chuckles]

09:41.707 --> 09:43.917
- THE MONKEY SAID
TO HIS SISTER,

09:43.917 --> 09:47.630
"I DON'T WANT TO BUY BANANAS
FROM THAT MAN."

09:47.630 --> 09:49.881
- KNOCK, KNOCK.

09:49.881 --> 09:51.216
VISITORS.

09:51.216 --> 09:52.677
- GOOD MORNING.

09:52.677 --> 09:54.344
- HEY, SHEILA.

09:54.344 --> 09:56.138
- HI.
- HI.

09:56.138 --> 09:59.725
- [gasps] LOOK WHO'S HERE.
- OH, MY GOD.

09:59.725 --> 10:01.727
- I GOT SOME SPECIAL TREATS.

10:01.727 --> 10:04.104
- OH.
- OOH!

10:04.104 --> 10:06.440
- VERY NICE.
- A LITTLE CARE PACKAGE.

10:06.440 --> 10:08.108
HOW'S THE PATIENT?

10:08.108 --> 10:10.695
- WELL, HE STILL HASN'T
WOKEN UP YET.

10:10.695 --> 10:11.653
- [gasps]

10:11.653 --> 10:14.573
HMM.

10:14.573 --> 10:17.200
FRANK.

10:17.200 --> 10:18.368
FRANKIE.

10:18.368 --> 10:19.453
FRANKIE, FRANKIE, FRANKIE,

10:19.453 --> 10:21.163
FRANK-A, FRANK,
FRANK, FRANKIE.

10:21.163 --> 10:23.165
HUH.

10:23.165 --> 10:24.583
FRANK?

10:24.583 --> 10:25.876
WOW.

10:27.627 --> 10:29.713
FRANK.

10:29.713 --> 10:33.717
FRANK, WHERE ARE YOU?

10:33.717 --> 10:36.136
FRANK, IT'S ME, SHEILA.

10:36.136 --> 10:39.681
COME OUT, COME OUT,
WHEREVER YOU ARE.

10:39.681 --> 10:42.685
YOU HAVE GOT TO WAKE UP.

10:42.685 --> 10:46.563
YOU SEE, YOU HAVE
SOME HUSBANDLY DUTIES

10:46.563 --> 10:47.690
TO ATTEND TO.

10:47.690 --> 10:48.691
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!

10:48.691 --> 10:50.108
YOU CAN'T BE UP THERE.

10:50.108 --> 10:51.485
YOU'RE GONNA KNOCK OUT
HIS I.V. TUBES OUT.

10:51.485 --> 10:53.070
COME ON.
- NO, I'M NOT.

10:53.070 --> 10:55.572
- THE NURSES AND DOCTORS
ARE DOING EVERYTHING THEY CAN,

10:55.572 --> 10:56.740
AND YOU JUST NEED
TO LET HIM REST.

10:56.740 --> 10:58.575
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
HE'S BEEN RESTING.

10:58.575 --> 11:00.035
- OKAY, SO CAN YOU GET DOWN?

11:00.035 --> 11:02.162
- I'M TRYING TO GET HIM UP,
FOR GOD SAKES.

11:02.162 --> 11:05.582
LISTEN, THESE ARE
HIS SOON-TO-BE CHILDREN,

11:05.582 --> 11:06.750
AND I'M HIS WIFE.

11:06.750 --> 11:08.585
SO JUST TAKE
A BREATHER, MISSY.

11:08.585 --> 11:09.669
- UH-HUH.

11:09.669 --> 11:10.754
- ISN'T THAT RIGHT, GUYS?

11:10.754 --> 11:12.923
- MM-HMM.
- RIGHT-O.

11:12.923 --> 11:15.842
WE COULD DO A NATIVE AMERICAN
INDIAN TRIBAL DANCE

11:15.842 --> 11:17.677
TO WAKE HIM,
MAMA SHEILA.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.679
- [gasps]
WHAT'S THAT?

11:19.679 --> 11:21.181
- WE LEARNED ABOUT IT

11:21.181 --> 11:23.433
IN OUR CULTURAL HISTORY CLASS
AT SCHOOL.

11:23.433 --> 11:26.019
- I WISH I COULD GO TO SCHOOL.

11:26.019 --> 11:27.813
- [gasps]

11:27.813 --> 11:29.857
- MIND YOUR MANNERS, EMILY.

11:29.857 --> 11:31.733
I-I'M SO SORRY.
SHE DIDN'T MEAN TO EAVESDROP.

