17:56.451 --> 17:58.119
- WHAT? WHY?

17:58.119 --> 18:00.205
- I BETTER GET THE DOCTOR.

18:00.205 --> 18:02.207
- WHERE'S MAMA GOING, LIP?

18:02.207 --> 18:05.210
- DUDE, WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?
I'M CARL.

18:05.210 --> 18:06.586
MAYBE I SHOULD HIT HIM
IN THE NUTS AGAIN--

18:06.586 --> 18:07.879
- AH! NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

18:07.879 --> 18:09.047
- HE'S AWAKE!

18:09.047 --> 18:10.632
JUST LIKE I TOLD YOU.

18:10.632 --> 18:11.841
- THIS IS GOOD NEWS.

18:11.841 --> 18:13.760
A LOT SOONER
THAN EXPECTED.

18:13.760 --> 18:15.053
- HE THINKS
WE'RE DIFFERENT PEOPLE.

18:15.053 --> 18:16.763
YOU SCREWED HIS BRAIN ON
BACKWARDS.

18:16.763 --> 18:19.015
- FRANK, DO YOU KNOW
WHERE YOU ARE?

18:19.015 --> 18:20.600
YOU'RE IN
THE INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

18:20.600 --> 18:22.560
AT ST. MICHAEL HOSPITAL.

18:22.560 --> 18:25.021
YOU UNDERWENT SURGERY
A FEW DAYS AGO

18:25.021 --> 18:26.273
FOR YOUR LIVER.

18:26.273 --> 18:28.233
- MAMA, WHAT'S HE TALKING ABOUT?

18:28.233 --> 18:29.609
- SEE? WHAT'D I TELL YOU?

18:29.609 --> 18:31.444
- WHY DOES HE THINK
WE'RE DIFFERENT PEOPLE?

18:31.444 --> 18:33.155
- UH, LET'S GO OUT IN THE HALL
AND TALK.

18:33.155 --> 18:35.532
- OKAY, WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
HOLD ON.

18:37.909 --> 18:41.663
- MR. GALLAGHER IS SUFFERING
FROM POSTOPERATIVE DELIRIUM.

18:41.663 --> 18:43.665
- OKAY, WHAT'S THAT?

18:43.665 --> 18:45.209
- IT OFTEN HAPPENS

18:45.209 --> 18:47.085
WHEN A PATIENT
UNDERGOES INTENSE SURGERY

18:47.085 --> 18:49.837
WHERE A HEAVY DOSE OF SEDATION
WAS USED.

18:49.837 --> 18:52.423
- OH.
IS IT--IS IT PERMANENT?

18:52.423 --> 18:53.883
- UH, NO.

18:53.883 --> 18:55.677
IT'S VERY COMMON
IN POST-OP PATIENTS.

18:55.677 --> 18:58.805
HE'LL BE CONFUSED ABOUT TIME
AND RELATIONSHIPS.

18:58.805 --> 19:00.473
ALL YOU CAN DO IS BE PATIENT

19:00.473 --> 19:02.267
WHILE HE'S
IN THIS ALTERED STATE,

19:02.267 --> 19:05.019
BUT HE'LL BE BACK
TO HIS OLD SELF SOON.

19:06.187 --> 19:07.313
- OH, SHOOT.

19:07.313 --> 19:09.190
